From: Pulse Audit <audit@pulse.local>
Subject: [PATCH] fix(check-in): plan volgende ISO-week, niet de review-week

The check-in wizard incorrectly planned for the same ISO-week that was being
reviewed. Root cause: CheckInFlow passed data.week.weekStart/weekEnd straight
through to <WeekPlanCard>, with no +7-day offset. Combined with a UTC-based
getWeekStart helper that goes off-by-one for Europe/Amsterdam users between
00:00–02:00 local time, the wizard could plan for a week that was already
14 days in the past around DST boundaries.

This patch:
- adds src/lib/dates/week.ts with TZ-safe helpers (Europe/Amsterdam, date-fns/tz)
- replaces inline getWeekStart/getWeekEnd/getISOWeekNumber in 4 routes
- propagates planWeekStart/planWeekEnd through CheckInFlow → WeekPlanCard
- accepts plan_week_start in /api/check-in/confirm and uses it for
  updateScheduledOverrides instead of the review week
- adds tests covering Sunday-evening, early-Monday-CET, DST start, DST end

